 The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":16,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Lancaster was born about 1366, in Sockbridge and Tirril, Westmorland, England, his father, William Lancaster Knt., was 23 and his mother, Margaret Warcop, was 20. He had at least 2 sons with Christian Salkeld. He died in 1404, in his hometown, at the age of 39."},"et":{"Abt 1366–1404":"umbes 1366–1404","1366–1404":"1366–1404","1370–Female":"1370–Surnud","1400–1483":"1400–1483","1405–Male":"1405–Surnud","1345–Male":"1345–Surnud","1348–Female":"1348–Surnud","1404":"1404","1348":"1348","Abt 1366":"umbes 1366","1400":"1400","1345":"1345","1366":"1366","1483":"1483","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1405":"1405","Sockbridge, Westmorland, England":"Sockbridge and Tirril, Westmorland, England","Lancaster, Lancashire, England":"Lancaster, Lancashire, England","Sockbridge and Tirril, Westmorland, England":"Sockbridge and Tirril, Westmorland, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1366–1404":"noin 1366–1404","1366–1404":"1366–1404","1370–Female":"1370–Kuollut","1400–1483":"1400–1483","1405–Male":"1405–Kuollut","1345–Male":"1345–Kuollut","1348–Female":"1348–Kuollut","1404":"1404","1348":"1348","Abt 1366":"noin 1366","1400":"1400","1345":"1345","1366":"1366","1483":"1483","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1405":"1405","Sockbridge, Westmorland, England":"Sockbridge and Tirril, Westmorland, England","Lancaster, Lancashire, England":"Lancaster, Lancashire, E